# Low-Code Specific Rules
- Assume limited unit testing; compensate with:
  - API contract checks where possible
  - Smoke tests for golden paths
  - Data integrity probes (DB/API) after UI actions
- Always require test IDs (data-testid) for new UI elements.
- Avoid brittle selectors (text-only, nth-child).
